<item>
            <title>[LU-778] RHEL 6.2: rdma_create_id() takes four arguments</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-778</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As of RHEL6.2 kernel 2.6.32-204.el6, rdma_create_id() requires a queue pair type as a fourth argument.  This was previously inferred from the rdma_port_space argument. Consequently, ko2iblnd fails to build on this kernel.  We have a patch to address this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL 6.2</environment>
        <key id="12188">LU-778</key>
            <summary>RHEL 6.2: rdma_create_id() takes four arguments</summary>
